cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL

This paper proposes a new activation function for deep neural networks and evaluates its performance on various datasets. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the experiments are conducted on image classification datasets, indicating a potential fit for cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the impact of the activation function on task performance, suggesting a possible fit for cs.LG (Machine Learning). The proposed activation function is a simple modification of the sigmoid function, which is a fundamental concept in artificial intelligence, indicating a potential fit for cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the practical implications of the proposed activation function, suggesting a possible fit for cs.CL (Computation and Language).
